<subSubSection pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="434">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="434">Note:</emphasis>
Some authors (e.g. Fernald in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="434">Rhodora</emphasis>
42: 436. 1940) have accepted 
<bibRefCitation pageNumber="434" refId="references.r66">Clarke (1881)</bibRefCitation>
as having typified the name (though this is open to doubt) using the cited Dillenian plate, though Hunt (in McVaugh, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="434">Fl. Novo-Galiciana</emphasis>
13: 144. 1993) has more recently thrown doubt on the taxonomic identity of this element. Morton (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="434">Bot. J. Linn. Soc.</emphasis>
60: 183. 1967) treated 65.6 (LINN) as the type but the identity of this, too, has been questioned (see Rao &amp; al. in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="434">Bot. J. Linn. Soc.</emphasis>
60: 360. 1968).
</paragraph>
